{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/linear-story/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"fridge notes"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c2a15b8b-a874-5b7e-bdad-7ebdd6ab1ac1","excerpt":"look here for the story inspiration something i’ve been interested in is rumination and memory. i’ve been trying to expel my own thoughts onto paper. so, i…","html":"<p><a href=\"http://samheckle.com/hosted/linear/\">look here for the story</a></p>\n<h2>inspiration</h2>\n<p>something i’ve been interested in is rumination and memory. i’ve been trying to expel my own thoughts onto paper. so, i wanted to use inform 7 to actually go physically backwards in a memory, and try and trace the map of how this would be represented with text.</p>\n<p>i’ve also been reading a lot about memory (cc <em>dirk gently’s holistic detective agency</em> by douglas adams and <em>mcglue</em> by ottessa moshfegh) which i would also recommend for no other reason than pleasure.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/29114/quotes.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"quotes\"\n        title=\"quotes\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/fcda8/quotes.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/12f09/quotes.png 148w,\n/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/e4a3f/quotes.png 295w,\n/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/fcda8/quotes.png 590w,\n/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/efc66/quotes.png 885w,\n/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/c83ae/quotes.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/c70fd35d9cce394d83f18043ff542093/29114/quotes.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>process</h2>\n<p>i started with the shape of the map i wanted first. something i’ve noticed when writing these interactive fictions is thinking about the whole story and the shape rather than the individual details. </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/29114/map.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"map\"\n        title=\"map\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/fcda8/map.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/12f09/map.png 148w,\n/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/e4a3f/map.png 295w,\n/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/fcda8/map.png 590w,\n/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/efc66/map.png 885w,\n/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/c83ae/map.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/f873a0c1e4836a4264728dcd721721d6/29114/map.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>i wanted to have something that was cyclical — the start and the end being the same. </p>\n<p>each “room” manifested themselves as a part of the thought process. ideas manifest themselves as containers that you can go into. they change each time you enter the idea as well, as demonstrated below.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/29114/after.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"after\"\n        title=\"after\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/fcda8/after.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/12f09/after.png 148w,\n/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/e4a3f/after.png 295w,\n/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/fcda8/after.png 590w,\n/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/efc66/after.png 885w,\n/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/c83ae/after.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/f216aaa984b789efb1524705db3e5706/29114/after.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>final</h2>\n<p>i ended up breaking my story into separate sections, each with their respective room. i didn’t play around too much with items but i might continue to do that later.</p>\n<p>list of rooms: Death, Revelation, Spiraling, Thoughts, Decision, Naming, Birth</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://samheckle.com/hosted/linear/\">look here for the story again</a></p>\n<hr>\n<h1>resources</h1>\n<p><a href=\"http://inform7.com/book/RB_3_2.html\">inform map docs</a>\n<a href=\"http://inform7.com/book/WI_17_1.html\">inform understand docs</a>\n<a href=\"https://intfiction.org/t/multiple-rooms-inside-another/10642\">multiple rooms inside another</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/Inform7/comments/lzlj7f/how_to_iterate_through_list_of_values/\">iterating through list</a>\n<a href=\"http://inform7.com/book/RB_11_6.html\">inform end docs</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"a linear story","date":"April 04, 2022","description":"assignment #4 in inform 7"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/linear-story/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/generated-twilight/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"blackout poetry"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/generated-poems-on-intimacy/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"markov chains"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","3257411868"]}